'''天使降臨之頂'''是一個位於美國[[猶他州|猶他州]]南部[[錫安國家公園|錫安國家公園]]的石頭山，高度454公尺（約1488英呎）。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nps.gov/featurecontent/zion/eHike.htm |title=Zion National Park eHike |access-date=2016-01-08 |archive-date=2021-02-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210205161146/https://www.nps.gov/featurecontent/zion/eHike.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref> 1926年規劃了一條深入巨石之間的登山道，讓人可以沿途攻頂，從天使降臨的頂端欣賞[[錫安峽谷|錫安峽谷]]的美景。

== 登山道 ==
天使降臨之頂的登山道約3.9公里（2.4英哩） <ref name="trail">[http://www.nps.gov/archive/zion/WalksAndHikesPages/AngelsLanding.htm Angels Landing Trail Information] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nps.gov/archive/zion/WalksAndHikesPages/AngelsLanding.htm |date=20090903193151 }} from the National Park System</ref>，始於錫安國家公園班車系統（早春到晚秋營運）「The Grotto」<ref name="mountainranges"><cite class="citation web" id="mountainranges" contenteditable="false">Lloyd, Tommy. </cite></ref> 。登山道一開始大致遵循維爾京河的路線，為沙地的緩坡，之後會經果幾個[[髮夾彎|髮夾彎]]，開始快速增加高度，而登山道也會穿越天使降臨之頂與錫安峽谷之間的上升路段。Walter's Wiggles有連續21個髮夾彎<ref name="trail">[http://www.nps.gov/archive/zion/WalksAndHikesPages/AngelsLanding.htm Angels Landing Trail Information] from the National Park System</ref> ，是要到達Scout Lookout的最後一個關卡。對於沒有要登上天使降臨之頂的登山客來說，Scout Lookout便是此行的終點了，而最後登頂的0.5英里非常困難，必須拉著鐵鍊手腳並用攀爬、並面對不少狹窄和急墜的路段。<ref name="trail">[http://www.nps.gov/archive/zion/WalksAndHikesPages/AngelsLanding.htm Angels Landing Trail Information] from the National Park System</ref>

根據[[美国国家公园管理局|美國國家公園管理局]]的說法，「前往天使降臨之頂的路線有陡峭、狹窄的山脊，沿途會有支撐用的鐵鍊協助攀爬；當石頭是乾燥的時候，立足點可能會易滑，在相鄰及墜處岩石表面刻有粗糙的立足點。當潮濕、結冰或雷雨時請不要踏入此地。天黑後也不要進行攀爬計畫。年幼的兒童不建議翻爬，而年齡較大的孩童則也需要嚴密的監督。<ref name="trail">[http://www.nps.gov/archive/zion/WalksAndHikesPages/AngelsLanding.htm Angels Landing Trail Information] from the National Park System</ref> <div>美國國家公園管理局的網站上官方承認了五名死亡人數，不過也有許多其他的死亡被報導。<ref><cite class="citation web" contenteditable="false">Kelly Burgess (30 November 2009). </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation web" contenteditable="false">[http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/lanow/2009/08/glendora-woman-plunges-1000-feet-to-death-in-utahs-zion-national-park.html "Glendora woman plunges 1,000 feet to death in Utah's Zion National Park"] {{Wayback|url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/lanow/2009/08/glendora-woman-plunges-1000-feet-to-death-in-utahs-zion-national-park.html |date=20201128170534 }}. </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation web" contenteditable="false">David Eaker (10 June 2007). </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation web" contenteditable="false">[http://www.ksl.com/?nid=148&sid=439979 "Woman Dead After Fall in Zion National Park"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ksl.com/?nid=148&sid=439979 |date=20160304001004 }}. </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation web" contenteditable="false">[http://www.usatoday.com/news/nation/2004-06-27-utah-teen_x.htm "California teen dies in fall at Utah park"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.usatoday.com/news/nation/2004-06-27-utah-teen_x.htm |date=20111214142737 }}. </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation web" contenteditable="false">[http://www.deseretnews.com/article/538873/BOTCHED-RAPPEL-BLAMED-IN-DEATH-OF-ZION-CLIMBER.html "Botched Rappel Blamed in Death of Zion Climber"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.deseretnews.com/article/538873/BOTCHED-RAPPEL-BLAMED-IN-DEATH-OF-ZION-CLIMBER.html |date=20181004103730 }}. </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation web" contenteditable="false">[http://www.deseretnews.com/article/41031/PRELIMINARY-AUTOPSY-SHOWS-NO-SIGN-OF-FOUL-PLAY-I